genresAdvancedInfo.name: old school nederhop
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Old school nederhop is a genre of Dutch hip hop that emerged in the late 1980s and early 1990s. It is characterized by its use of Dutch language lyrics and its focus on social and political issues facing the Netherlands. Old school nederhop has had a significant impact on the development of Dutch hip hop, and remains popular to this day.
